class Solution {
    public long maximumSubarraySum(int[] nums, int k) {
        long ans = 0;
        long sum = 0;
        Map<Integer, Long> map = new HashMap<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            sum += nums[i];
            if (i >= k) {
                sum -= nums[i - k];
            }
            if (i >= k - 1) {
                ans = Math.max(ans, sum);
            }
            map.put(nums[i], sum);
        }
        for (int i = k; i < nums.length; i++) {
            long temp = ans;
            if (map.containsKey(nums[i - k] + k)) {
                temp = Math.max(temp, map.get(nums[i - k] + k) + nums[i] - nums[i - k]);
            }
            ans = Math.max(ans, temp);
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```

In this code, we first calculate the sum of the subarray from the 0th to the ith element and store the sum in the map. Then we iterate over the array from the kth element to the end and for each element, we calculate the sum of the subarray ending at the current element and check if there is a previous subarray that has an absolute difference of k. If there is, we update the answer with the maximum of the current answer and the sum of the current subarray and the previous subarray with the difference of k.

Please note that the time complexity of this solution is O(n) and the space complexity is also O(n).

