class Solution {
    public int minOrAfterOperations(int[] nums, int k) {
        int ans = 0;
        int mask = 0;
        for (int b = 29; b >= 0; b--) {
            mask |= 1 << b;
            int cnt = 0; // 操作次数
            int or = 0; // 0 的二进制全为 0
            for (int x : nums) {
                or |= x & mask;
                if (or != mask) {
                    cnt++; // 合并 x，操作次数加一
                } else {
                    or = 0; // 准备合并下一段
                }
            }
            if (cnt > k) {
                ans |= (mask ^ 1 << b); // 答案的这个比特位必须是 0
                mask ^= 1 << b; // 后面不考虑这个比特位
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}

This solution works by iterating over each bit from the most significant to the least significant. It calculates the bitwise OR of all elements in nums and the mask, and checks if the OR is equal to the mask. If it is, then all elements in nums have their corresponding bit set. If it's not, then there exists some element in nums where the corresponding bit is not set.

If the count of elements where the corresponding bit is not set is greater than k, then the bit in the answer must be 0. Otherwise, the bit in the answer must be 1. The count of operations is then calculated by subtracting the count of elements where the corresponding bit is not set from k.

If the count of operations is greater than k, then it's not possible to achieve the minimum possible value. In this case, the function returns -1. Otherwise, the function returns the answer.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n * m), where n is the length of nums and m is the maximum value in nums. The space complexity is O(1), because only a constant amount of space is used.

