A: The problem you have to solve is about the parity of numbers. If Alice takes an even number of elements (i.e., even sum of numbers) then Bob can take the remaining odd number of elements (i.e., odd sum of numbers) to make the sum equal. Alice wins if she takes odd number of elements (i.e., odd sum of numbers) because she can subtract Bob's number from her own.

In this case, Alice can win if the sum of all numbers in the list is odd. Therefore, we can return True if the sum of all numbers in the list is odd, and False otherwise.

